items.content: # =================================================================== # # Script: Object_Scene # # $$COPYRIGHT$$ # # =================================================================== class Object_Scene extends gs.Object_Base # @objectCodecBlackList = ["parent", "subObjects", "preparing", "behavior", "interpreter", "events", "sceneData", # "characterContainer", "pictureContainer", "textContainer", "videoContainer", "messageAreas", "hotspotContainer", "commonEventContainer", # "pictures", "texts", "videos", "messageAreas", "hotspots", "commonEvents", "layout", "layoutNVL"] @accessors "visible", set: (v) -> if v != @visible_ @visible_ = v @needsUpdate = yes @fullRefresh() get: -> @visible_ and (!@parent or @parent.visible) ###* * A scene object manages a whole visual novel scene with backgrounds, characters, * messages, etc. * * @module vn * @class Object_Scene * @extends gs.Object_Base * @memberof vn * @constructor ### constructor: -> super() ###* * Indicates that the scene is still in prepare-state and not ready yet. * @property preparing * @type boolean ### @preparing = yes ###* * The behavior-component for the VN scene specific behavior. * @property behavior * @type gs.Component_GameSceneBehavior ### @behavior = new vn.Component_GameSceneBehavior() ###* * An interpreter to execute the commands of scene. * @property interpreter * @type gs.Component_CommandInterpreter ### @interpreter = new gs.Component_CommandInterpreter() ###* * An event-emitter to emit events. * @property events * @type gs.Component_EventEmitter ### @events = new gs.Component_EventEmitter() ###* * Contains all background objects of the scene. * @property backgroundContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @backgroundContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all character objects of the scene. * @property characterContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @characterContainer = new gs.Object_Container(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.REMOVE) ###* * Contains all picture objects of the scene. * @property pictureContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @pictureContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all video objects of the scene. * @property videoContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @videoContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all text objects of the scene. * @property textContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @textContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all hotspot objects of the scene. * @property hotspotContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @hotspotContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all common events which are running parallel/auto to the scene. * @property commonEventContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @commonEventContainer = new gs.Object_Container(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all viewports which are used to create multi-layered screen effects. * @property viewportContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @viewportContainer = new gs.Object_Container(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.REMOVE) ###* * Contains all interval timers. * @property timerContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @timerContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) ###* * Contains all message areas of the scene. * @property messageAreaContainer * @type gs.Object_Container ### @messageAreaContainer = new gs.Object_DomainContainer(gs.ContainerDisposeBehavior.NULL) @characterContainer.visible = yes ###* * All picture objects as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property pictures * @type gs.Object_Picture[] * @readOnly ### @pictures = @pictureContainer.subObjects ###* * All video objects as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property videos * @type gs.Object_Video[] * @readOnly ### @videos = @videoContainer.subObjects ###* * All text objects as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property texts * @type gs.Object_Text[] * @readOnly ### @texts = @textContainer.subObjects ###* * All character objects as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property characters * @type gs.Object_Character[] * @readOnly ### @characters = @characterContainer.subObjects ###* * All backgrounds as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property backgrounds * @type gs.Object_Background[] * @readOnly ### @backgrounds = @backgroundContainer.subObjects ###* * All hotspot objects as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property hotspots * @type gs.Object_Hotspot[] * @readOnly ### @hotspots = @hotspotContainer.subObjects ###* * All interval timer objects as array. That is the same like accessing the subObjects of the * container object. * @property timers * @type gs.Object_IntervalTimer[] * @readOnly ### @timers = @timerContainer.subObjects ###* * All message areas as array. * @property messageAreas * @type vn.MessageArea[] * @readOnly ### @messageAreas = @messageAreaContainer.subObjects ###* * A timer object used for choices with time-limit. * @property choiceTimer * @type gs.Object_Timer ### @choiceTimer = new gs.Object_Timer() ###* * Indicates if the UI layout is visible. * @property visible * @type boolean ### @visible = yes ###* * @property visible_ * @type boolean * @protected ### @visible_ = yes ###* * The game settings. * @property settings * @type Object ### @settings = GameManager.settings ###* * Temporary settings like skip, etc. * @property tempSettings * @type Object ### @tempSettings = GameManager.settings ###* * Contains all data necessary to construct the scene. * @property sceneData * @type Object ### @sceneData = GameManager.sceneData @addObject(@backgroundContainer) @addObject(@characterContainer) @addObject(@pictureContainer) @addObject(@textContainer) @addObject(@videoContainer) @addObject(@hotspotContainer) @addObject(@viewportContainer) @addObject(@commonEventContainer) @addObject(@timerContainer) @addObject(@choiceTimer) @addObject(@messageAreaContainer) @addComponent(new gs.Component_InputHandler()) @addComponent(@behavior) @addComponent(@interpreter) vn.Object_Scene = Object_Scene
